<section class="py-16 bg-white"><div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><h2 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What We Build</h2><p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Every property drains differently. We assess where water enters your lot, where it pools, and where it needs to exit — then we build the infrastructure to make that happen reliably every storm.</p>
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6"><div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Catch Basins</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Collect surface water at low points and route it underground through solid pipe to a discharge point.</p></div><div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Channel Drains</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Linear grate drains across driveways, patios, and walkways to intercept sheet flow before it enters your home.</p></div><div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Dry Creek Beds</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Decorative rock channels that move water during storms and look like a natural landscape feature when dry.</p></div><div class="bg-green-50 rounded-xl p-6"><h3 class="font-heading font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Grading & Berms</h3><p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Reshaping the ground to direct water away from structures. Sometimes the simplest fix is the most effective.</p></div></div></div></section>

